I"Ä<p>One of the simplest methods in evaluating exact values of trigonometric functions is by using the unit circle. The unit circle is a circle in a cartesian plane with a radius of one and has a center located on the origin. Angles in a unit circle are measured from the positive $x$-axis, with clockwise rotation resulting to a positive angle, and counter-clockwise direction to a negative angle.</p>

<figure style="text-align: center;">
